Place chopped rosemary and vinegar in medium bowl. Let stand 15 minutes. Whisk in mayonnaise and garlic. Season rosemary mayonnaise to taste with salt and pepper. (Can be made 2 days ahead. Cover and keep refrigerated.) Line large platter with romaine leaves. Arrange roast beef atop lettuce. Sprinkle with onion slices, if desired. Serve roast beef and rosemary mayonnaise separately.